<div class="bm-faq-wrapper color-scheme-dark-luxury" id="faq">
  <div class="bm-faq-inner">
    <h2 class="bm-faq-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    {% assign faqs = 
      "
      What if I'm not sure how to describe what I want?||
      You don't need musical language or a fully formed concept ‚Äî that's what my process is for.
      <br><br>
      A short questionnaire and a guided chat help me understand the person, story, and emotion behind the song.
      <br><br>
      From there, I translate your answers into a clear creative direction so you never feel responsible for 'directing' the music.

      ---
      How do you make sure the first version is right?||
      Most of the work happens before I start composing.
      <br><br>
      The survey, our conversation, and any reference points you share give me a strong sense of tone, pacing, and emotional arc.
      <br><br>
      I treat the first version as a finished piece ‚Äî not a draft ‚Äî so when you hear it, it should feel intentional, polished, and true to what you shared.

      ---
      What happens if the creative direction doesn't feel right?||
      If the song feels emotionally off ‚Äî the vibe, energy, or tone isn't matching your vision ‚Äî we talk about what feels misaligned.
      <br><br>
      I don't offer endless tiny technical edits. Instead, I focus on meaningful creative alignment, shifting the mood or direction so the piece feels honest and expressive.
      <br><br>
      The goal is clarity and emotional truth, not mechanical tweaking.

      ---
      Can I request changes?||
      Yes ‚Äî when the changes are meaningful.
      <br><br>
      If hearing the song makes you realize the emotion or style needs to lean in a different direction, we address that thoughtfully.
      <br><br>
      I don't provide mix-by-mix or engineering revisions, but I absolutely welcome feedback that helps bring the artistic direction into clearer focus.

      ---
      Who owns the rights to my song?||
      You receive broad permission to use and share your commissioned song in any normal personal or creative context ‚Äî including posting online, playing it at events, or sharing it with friends and family.
      <br><br>
      I don't resell your commissioned piece, and anything personal you share with me always remains yours.
      <br><br>
      I create each piece using my own writing and direction, supported by professional digital production tools. Because different platforms have evolving terms, I don't make legal guarantees for large-scale commercial uses like national advertising, film/TV placements, or major-label releases.
      <br><br>
      For everyday personal and online use, you're fully covered. If you ever plan a major commercial release, I'm happy to provide documentation of my creative role so you (or your legal advisor) can confirm everything aligns with current guidelines.
      <br><br>
      I reserve the right to use short excerpts of the work in my portfolio or marketing unless you request complete privacy.

      ---
      Will the song feel artificial because AI is involved?||
      AI is simply the instrument used to perform and render the music ‚Äî not the author.
      <br><br>
      I write the lyrics, shape the melody, define the emotional tone, and guide how the performance should feel.
      <br><br>
      The technology helps produce the final delivery, but the meaning, structure, and creative decisions behind the song are fully human.
      <br><br>
      The finished piece should feel personal, expressive, and emotionally grounded ‚Äî not artificial or generic.

      ---
      What is your refund policy?||
      I want the experience to feel fair, transparent, and comfortable.
      <br><br>
      Because each song is handcrafted and tailored to your story, the refund structure follows the natural checkpoints of the creative process:
      <br><br>
      <strong>‚Ä¢ Before final lyric approval:</strong> Full refund ‚Äî no questions asked.<br>
      <strong>‚Ä¢ After lyric approval but before the first musical rendering:</strong> 50% refund.<br>
      <strong>‚Ä¢ After the first musical rendering:</strong> 25% refund.<br>
      <strong>‚Ä¢ After the second musical edit:</strong> The work is considered complete and non-refundable.<br><br>
      These stages protect you without locking you in, and I always encourage early communication so we can address any misalignment as soon as it appears.
      "
    | split: "---" %}

    {% for faq in faqs %}
      {% assign parts = faq | split: "||" %}
      <div class="bm-faq-item">
        <button class="bm-faq-question" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open')">
          <span class="bm-faq-icon">ùÑû</span>
          {{ parts[0] | strip }}
        </button>
        <div class="bm-faq-answer">
          <p>{{ parts[1] }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</div>

<style>
  .bm-faq-wrapper {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #1a1a1a 0%, #1a1715 100%);
    padding: 100px 0;
    color: #f5f5f5;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(212, 175, 55, 0.1);
  }
  
  .bm-faq-inner {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 24px;
  }

  .bm-faq-title {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 42px;
    font-size: 34px;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    font-family: "Playfair Display", serif;
    color: #D4AF37;
    text-shadow: 0 2px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
  }

  .bm-faq-item {
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(212, 175, 55, 0.15);
    padding: 16px 0;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }
  
  .bm-faq-item:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .bm-faq-question {
    width: 100%;
    text-align: left;
    background: none;
    border: none;
    padding: 16px 0;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    cursor: pointer;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 16px;
    color: #f5f5f5;
    font-family: "Inter", sans-serif;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }
  
  .bm-faq-question:hover {
    color: #D4AF37;
    transform: translateX(4px);
  }

  .bm-faq-icon {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 24px;
    height: 24px;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    transition: transform 0.3s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
    color: #D4AF37;
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  .bm-faq-question.open .bm-faq-icon {
    transform: rotate(90deg);
    opacity: 1;
  }
  
  .bm-faq-question.open {
    color: #D4AF37;
  }

  .bm-faq-answer {
    display: none;
    padding: 0 16px 24px 40px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    opacity: 0.9;
    color: #cccccc;
    animation: fadeIn 0.4s ease;
  }
  
  @keyframes fadeIn {
    from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(-5px); }
    to { opacity: 0.9; transform: translateY(0); }
  }

  .bm-faq-answer strong {
    color: #D4AF37;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .bm-faq-question.open + .bm-faq-answer {
    display: block;
  }
  
  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .bm-faq-title { font-size: 28px; }
    .bm-faq-question { font-size: 1.05rem; }
    .bm-faq-answer { font-size: 0.95rem; }
  }
</style>

